restaurants.name: Amo
restaurants.carPark: Clark Quay Central, Roadside Public Parking
restaurants.description: Amò t presents an extraordinary communal Italian feast of antipasti, artisan pastas, handcrafted pizzas and large plates to share. Amò pizzas are fresh, light and the product of years of mastering the art of slow dough fermentation and optimal cooking methods. Made with natural leaven, semolina and extra virgin olive oil, pizzas are baked in a stone wood- fired oven using specially sourced almond wood. Guests enjoy an all Italian wine list with over 20 wines by the glass in addition to a cocktail list inspired by classic Italian tipples. A former warehouse, Amò celebrates its heritage with a post-industrial design concept. An indoor private dining room is available in addition to a 40-seater outdoor courtyard for dining under the stars.
restaurants.title: Assistant Sales and Marketing Manager

restaurants.name: Art
restaurants.description:
An elegant Italian restaurant and bar with contemporary Italian cuisine by Michelin-star Chef-Restaurateur Beppe De Vito and Chef De Cuisine Andrea De Paola.
Art’s ingredient-driven menu is a continuous exploration of Italian tradition and its evolution. The menu is a creative expression of Beppe’s culinary philosophy that reflects his respect for Italy’s rich culinary heritage while looking forward through technical innovation.
An elegant bar features an extensive list of modern cocktails, spirits and one of the city’s best collections of Italian and French wine heavyweights.
Decked in fire engine red leather seats and well-lit by handmade brass sconces, Art showcases Italian culinary craftsmanship at its finest through luxury design, and world-class service.
restaurants.executiveChef: Beppe De Vito, Andrea De Paola
restaurants.title: Assistant Sales and Marketing Manager

restaurants.name: Aura
restaurants.address: 1 St. Andrews Road, #05-03 National Gallery Singapore
restaurants.description:
Spanning across the highest two floors of the iconic National Gallery, Aura is an elegant multi-concept dining establishment celebrating the passion for quality hospitality and cultural authenticity.
Inspired by homely Italian recipes, creations are refined and elevated to form an exquisite menu featuring the finest and freshest ingredients from land and sea.
One level up and guests can experience Aura’s sky lounge, a stylish 200 seater fronted by the spectacular Marina Bay Skyline.
restaurants.title: Assistant Sales and Marketing Manager

restaurants.name: Braci
restaurants.transportation: MRT – Raffles Place MRT Station (EW14/NS26) and Clarke Quay Station (NE5)
restaurants.description:
Perched on the top two floors of a restored heritage shophouse by the Singapore River, Braci is an exclusive Italian hideaway in the heart of Boat Quay The luxe 20-seater Michelin star restaurant and 30-seater bar features progressive Italian cuisine and classic cocktails, reinvented.
With a name that means ‘embers’ in Italian, Braci’s menu is inspired by wood. The use of the Josper oven and the shichirin redefines and uplifts classic Italian cuisine. Guests are treated to the sights, sounds and smells of a buzzing open kitchen where food takes centre stage and chefs focus on showcasing each ingredient to its fullest.
Braci’s outdoor rooftop bar one floor above provides sweeping views of the city skyline over the Singapore River.
restaurants.title: Assistant Sales and Marketing Manager

restaurants.name: Chef’s Table by Chef Stephan
restaurants.carPark: Maxwell House, Orchid Hotel, Roadside Public Parking
restaurants.description:
Founded by acclaimed Chef Stephan Zoisl, authenticity and spontaneity sit at the heart of Chef’s Table. The restaurant prides itself on a degustation-only offering showcasing unique one-of a-kind dishes.
With a menu that reveals a choice of 28 central ingredients that change daily, local producers direct each day’s creations based on what’s available and in season. All dishes feature herbs and microgreens grown in the restaurant’s dining room.
Chef Stephan and Head Chef Lorenz Raich prepare and present each course to your table. The space evokes a feeling of home, with high chairs that put you on the same level as the chefs for easy conversation. An exquisite selection of European wines is available with new vintages constantly on rotation.
restaurants.title: Chef

restaurants.name: JAAN
restaurants.address: Swissotel the Stamford Hotel, 2 Stamford Road, Level 70
restaurants.description:
Michelin star awarded JAAN has established itself as a gastronomic platform for handpicking and grooming exceptional culinary talents.
Chef de Cuisine Kirk Westaway channels his passion for natural flavours that are reminiscent of his childhood in England. Applying the philosophy ’Reinventing British’, his evolving menu embodies a philosophy to showcase seasonal British dining in a modern light.
Derived from the Cambodian word for 'bowl', The intimate 40 seat restaurant features an elegant private dining room.  A stunning Murano crystal chandelier spans the entire length of the ceiling. Its beauty is only outdone by two things: the breathtaking view of Singapore’s skyline as well as the exquisite culinary and service experience that have become the hallmark of JAAN.
restaurants.title: Food & Beverage Manager / Assistant Project Manager, F&B Sales

restaurants.name: Shahi Maharani
restaurants.address: 252 North Bridge Rd, #03–21B Raffles City Shopping Centre
restaurants.description:
Established in 1997, Shahi Maharani is recognised as one of the most prominent Indian restaurants in Singapore. The restaurant takes guests on a royal culinary journey with traditional North Indian cuisine inspired by prized recipes from Maharajas of the past.

An affair to remember, guests receive the regal treatment, savouring authentic Indian cuisine and live music amidst décor reminiscent of the royal palaces of India.
restaurants.accolades: Wine & Dine – Singapore’s Top Restaurants 1997 to 2016

SKAI is a lively contemporary grill situated on the 70th floor of Singapore’s acclaimed Swissotel the Stamford. The iconic city views, seamless service and bespoke beverages make for the perfect ambience to savour the new menu curated by Executive Chef Paul Hallett.

Guests enjoy an exquisite selection of prime cuts of beef and fresh seafood infused with delicate Japanese accents. Chef Hallett blends cutting edge techniques with a signature culinary style to create a truly personal and progressive fine grill offering.

restaurants.name: Tamarind Hill Singapore
restaurants.carPark: Public Carpark 2 mins walk from the Restaurant
restaurants.description:
Set within a historic colonial bungalow and perched atop the forested Labrador Nature Reserve, nature and heritage harmonise at Tamarind Hill to present a gastronomic escape away from the city.

With its timeless interiors, rustic-luxe décor, and epicurean dishes, the restaurant is an amalgamation of Asian and colonial influences, mirroring the city's storied past.

Indulge in over 100 Thai and Burmese creations prepared from the freshest ingredients by a team of Thai chefs.  Each chef has contributed a selection of heirloom recipes to create an extensive repertoire of traditional and modern dishes.  A selection of house-infused Gins, signature cocktails, and fine wines from over 11 countries are available to complement your meal.

restaurants.title: Sales Manager

restaurants.name: Xi Yan Private Dining
restaurants.description:
First conceived in 2000 by celebrity chef Jacky Yu, Xi Yan celebrates taste as a work of contemporary art. Chef Jacky has innovatively reinterpreted the traditional Chinese banquet with his modern take on Chinese food that seamlessly blends East and Asian cuisines.

Having pioneered the concept of private dining, the restaurant continues to offer an enticing selection of chef menus. A host of new signature dishes are created each year with a menu that changes bi-weekly. The design of the restaurant is one of a home art gallery with an emphasis placed on incorporating art into culinary presentation, serving plates and decor.

Xi Yan’s unique cuisine redefines the perception of Chinese food to create an exciting contemporary dining experience.
